## 1. DevOps Concepts

### *1. Continuous Integration (CI)*
CI is the practice of frequently integrating code into a shared repository. Automated builds and tests run after each change to improve stability and reduce integration issues.

### *2. Continuous Delivery (CD)*
CD ensures that every code change is automatically tested, validated, and ready for deployment. This improves software reliability and shortens release cycles.

### *3. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)*
IaC manages and provisions infrastructure using code instead of manual setups. It improves consistency, enables automation, and allows version-controlled infrastructure.

### *4. Containerization*
Containerization packages an application and all its dependencies into a standardized unit. Docker containers ensure consistent environments across development, testing, and production.

### *5. Monitoring & Logging*
Monitoring collects system and application metrics, while logging captures runtime events. Together, they support performance insights, troubleshooting, and operational reliability.

